               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-305-person2329">
                  JOHN 
                  GROOM
               <interp inst="t18270913-305-person2329" type="surname" value="GROOM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-305-person2329" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-305-person2329" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 3d of September, about nine o'clock at night, I was going along <placeName id="t18270913-305-crimeloc1696">Queen-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-305-crimeloc1696" type="placeName" value="Queen-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-305-crimeloc1696" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-305-off1694 t18270913-305-crimeloc1696"></join>, with my wife, and saw Scornell put his hand into a gentleman's pocket several times, and at last he got a handkerchief out; he put it under his coat, and then gave it to Stevens; I ran and collared Stevens - he dropped it; my partner took the others. Lilley and Stevens were close behind, covering him, when he took it; we had a scuffle with them, and could not find the gentleman; Lilley must have seen him pass it to Stevens.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-305-person2330">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WHITTINGHAM
               <interp inst="t18270913-305-person2330" type="surname" value="WHITTINGHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-305-person2330" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-305-person2330" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Queen-street, and saw the three prisoners following the gentleman; I crossed over, and seized Scornell and Lilley, who were running.</p>
               <p>SCORNELL's Defence. The handkerchief was laying down - I was going to take it up, but Stevens did.</p>
               <p>STEVENS' Defence. I picked it up.</p>
               <p>Stevens received a good character.</p>
